We recommended:

For the optimal utilization of the LDRRM Fund to strengthen the resilience of the constituents to disaster and climate change impacts.  Disbursement against the fund should be in pursuance of RA No. 10121;

For the creation and filling up of the required four plantilla positions to manage and operate the local MDDRM Office in compliance with the NDRRMC-DILG-DBM-CSC Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2014-01 dated April 4, 2014;
That the LDRRM Officer (a) attend and conduct trainings and seminars to enhance the skill set of the MDRRMO personnel pursuant to the Disaster Preparedness Minimum Standards; and (b) prepare and submit inventory of existing MDRRM equipages to be able to identify the lacking DRRM equipment, tools and paraphernalia and utilize the LDRRM Fund for the acquisition of equipment in compliance with the minimum standards and pursuant to DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-73.
